headline: HCA Q3 Deep Dive: Medicaid Payments, Volume Growth, and Outlook Shape Results
summary: Hospital operator HCA Healthcare (NYSE:HCA) reported Q3 CY2025 results exceeding the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 9.6% year on year to $19.16 billion. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $75.75 billion at the midpoint came in 0.9% above analysts’ estimates. Its GAAP profit of $6.96 per share was 22.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
